The medicine works by immobilizing the parasites and preventing their survival, allowing the body to clear the infection more effectively.
dosage:
Ivecop-12 mg is usually taken as a single dose on an empty stomach with water, or as recommended by a licensed healthcare professional.
In some infections, a repeat dose may be required after medical evaluation.

Do not exceed the prescribed dose.

name: Menbendazole 500 mg
usage: Mebentel 500 mg Tablets are used to treat intestinal worm infections such as roundworms (Ascaris lumbricoides), hookworm, and whipworm infections. Mebendazole acts by stopping the worms from absorbing nutrients, causing them to die and pass out of the body. It helps relieve symptoms like stomach pain, diarrhea, and itching. This medicine should be taken only as directed by a healthcare professional.
dosage:
The usual recommended dosage for adults and children above 2 years is:

1 tablet of Mebentel 500 mg taken as a single dose.
Chew the tablet completely before swallowing.
Do not swallow whole.

Optional method for patients who cannot chew:

Place tablet on a spoon and add 2–3 mL water.

After 2 minutes it softens and can be swallowed easily.

details.value: Store in a cool, dry place away from sunlight
